  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up then put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667398572535-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667398572535-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667398572535-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667398572535-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667398572535-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>into rounds then wash thoroughly to remove any grit</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667398577774-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667398577774-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667398577774-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667398577774-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667398577774-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the potatoes have had 20 min, remove the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the oven and crush them lightly with a fork</p><p>Pat the <strong>smoked</strong> <strong>basa fillets</strong> dry with kitchen paper then add to the baking tray along with the <strong>chopped leek</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through and the potatoes are tender</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667398583856-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667398583856-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667398583856-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667398583856-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667398583856-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fish is cooking, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>milk stock</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> chives </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667398589959-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667398589959-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667398589959-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667398589959-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667398589959-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> butter</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your<strong> roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667398593998-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667398593998-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667398593998-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667398593998-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667398593998-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>milk stock</strong> to the<strong> </strong>roux<strong> </strong>gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Remove from the heat, add most of the <strong>chopped chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>herby white sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667398597918-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667398597918-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667398597918-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667398597918-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667398597918-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil the kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Once the fish is cooked, add the <strong>refreshed peas</strong> to the baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> – this is your <strong>fish pie tray bake</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667398603432-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667398603432-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667398603432-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667398603432-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667398603432-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fish pie tray bake </strong>and drizzle the <strong>herby white sauce </strong>over everything</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped chives</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
